Package edu.iit.ir.simpledm.exception

Provides exception classes for handling errors such as unassigned object exceptions, unsupported attribute type or class type exception, and missing categorical ID exception.

See:
          Description

Exception Summary
MissingCategoricalIDException MissingCategoricalIDException is used when a method is called that requires access to CategoricalAttributeValue, but that the id of the object is not available.
SimpleDMException SimpleDMException is used when some SimpleDM-specific checked exception must be raised.
UnassignedClassException UnassignedClassException is used when a method requires access to the Attribute in a DataSet but the DataSet does not have such an attribute assigned.
UnassignedDatasetException UnassignedDatasetException is used when a method is called that requires access to the DataSet, but that the DataSet does not exists.
UnsupportedAttributeTypeException UnsupportedAttributeTypeException is used in situations where the throwing object is not able to accept Attributes with the supplied structure, because one or more of the Attributes in the DataSet are of the wrong type.
UnsupportedClassTypeException UnsupportedClassTypeException is used in situations where the throwing object is not able to accept DataSet with the supplied structure, because the class Attribute is of the wrong type.
 

Package edu.iit.ir.simpledm.exception Description

Provides exception classes for handling errors such as unassigned object exceptions, unsupported attribute type or class type exception, and missing categorical ID exception. A programmer can extend any exception extending SimpleDMException.
